The paper focuses on quality assurance of software requirements specifications, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of clone detection, a technique widely applied to source code, suggests a potential overlap with programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The large-scale case study and evaluation of existing clone detection approaches may also involve machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques, which are relevant to the information systems (cs.SI) sub-category.
